Synchronous arytenoid and pancreatic neuroendocrine carcinoma.
 Neuroendocrine laryngeal carcinoid tumours are uncommon.
 The supraglottis is the main location of these tumours.
 Eighty-one cases have been reported in the world literature.
 We present the first case of a synchronous laryngeal and pancreatic neuroendocrine tumour.
